#content
  %h1
    %img{ :src => 'apple-touch-icon-114x114-precomposed.png' }/
    A Brand New <code>nanoc +<br />
    HTML5 Boilerplate</code> Site

  %p
    You’ve just created a new <code>nanoc + HTML5 Boilerplate site</code>. The
    page you are looking at right now is the home page for your site. To get
    started, consider replacing this default homepage with your own customized
    homepage. Some pointers on how to do so:

  %ul
    %li
      %p
        <strong>Change this page’s content</strong> by editing the “index.haml”
        file in the “content” directory which uses
        #{link_to 'Haml', 'http://haml-lang.com/'}. This is the actual page
        content, and therefore doesn’t include the header, sidebar or style
        information (those are part of the layout).
    %li
      %p
        <strong>Change the layout</strong>, which is the “default.haml” file in
        the “layouts” directory which uses
        #{link_to 'Haml', 'http://haml-lang.com/'} and is based on the
        #{link_to 'HTML5 Boilerplate', 'http://html5boilerplate.com/'}
        template.
    %li
      %p
        <strong>Change the style</strong>, which is the “style.scss” file in
        the “content/css” directory which uses
        #{link_to 'Sass', 'http://sass-lang.com/'},
        #{link_to 'Compass', 'http://compass-style.org/'} and
        #{link_to 'HTML5 Boilerplate', 'http://html5boilerplate.com/'}.
 
  %p
    If you need any help with customizing your <code>nanoc + HTML5 Boilerplate
    site</code> web site, be sure to check out the documentation (see sidebar),
    and be sure to subscribe to the discussion group (also see sidebar). Enjoy!

